    {
      "id": "yEcHlAvKiWjck4cSlc87l",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2157.202436810579,
      "y": 1247.0397784370193,
      "width": 795.6995849609375,
      "height": 950,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b73",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 896188000,
      "version": 1252,
      "versionNonce": 1923334048,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771597675344,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Deep dive 1: into how URL is generated??\n\nDeep dive 1: into how URL is generated??\n[0-9, a-z, A-Z] == 62 characters\n\nhttp://bitly.com/abcdefg\n\n365 bil unique shortURLs\n\n_      _       _\n62^1  62^2   62^3\n\n62 = ~64 == 2^6 => 6 bits\n365 bil => 1000 000 000 2^30 * 2^9 == 2^39\n6-7 characters (upperbound 7characters)\n\n{abcdefg: longUrl, ...}\n\nhow does our system then assign this hash\n\nsome_chars = hash(longURL)\nasdjhaksdhka\nasdjhak\nasdjhak => collision clash\n\nbad:\n- string too long => take first 7 characters\n- clash collisions => need to keep looking up DB to see if there is collision as well\n\n=> more elegant solution\nkeep a counter & use base 62 representation for the stirng\ncounter += 1\n11157 => 2TX\n- no collision\n- generate unique URL Ids for each DB instance => \n\nbad:\n- security concerns => predictable",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Deep dive 1: into how URL is generated??\n\nDeep dive 1: into how URL is generated??\n[0-9, a-z, A-Z] == 62 characters\n\nhttp://bitly.com/abcdefg\n\n365 bil unique shortURLs\n\n_      _       _\n62^1  62^2   62^3\n\n62 = ~64 == 2^6 => 6 bits\n365 bil => 1000 000 000 2^30 * 2^9 == 2^39\n6-7 characters (upperbound 7characters)\n\n{abcdefg: longUrl, ...}\n\nhow does our system then assign this hash\n\nsome_chars = hash(longURL)\nasdjhaksdhka\nasdjhak\nasdjhak => collision clash\n\nbad:\n- string too long => take first 7 characters\n- clash collisions => need to keep looking up DB to see if there is collision as well\n\n=> more elegant solution\nkeep a counter & use base 62 representation for the stirng\ncounter += 1\n11157 => 2TX\n- no collision\n- generate unique URL Ids for each DB instance => \n\nbad:\n- security concerns => predictable",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
